<div id="review_3138763859" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3138763859" />
    <a title="Kevin Reside" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/107778902-kevin-reside"><img alt="Kevin Reside" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1577781695p2/107778902.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3138763859?book_show_action=true">Jan 12, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kevin Reside" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kevin Reside" href="/user/show/107778902-kevin-reside">Kevin Reside</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140433319" href="/book/show/814670.On_Painting">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3138763859" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8086581876602289511">Had to read this book for an art class. “Book” 1 is a little jargon heavy and too technical for me, but books 2/3 lean a bit more into the romantic aspects of art and artists and are written in such a way that you feel compelled to go pick up a paint brush. At times it feels as though Alberti can’t help but pump his own tires, but had I contributed as much to the arts during one of its most known and respected periods I might be a little pompous too. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


