              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9565827364601213132">Strangely enough, I really liked this book, though I wouldn&apos;t call it a stimulating read. But it is the seminal book on painting in the Western world, and I was fascinated to read in archaic language some of the same elements of shape and form that I find in a modern book about drawing. This guy was the first to take a hands-on, heart-learned skill and make a manual for it. </span>
