<div id="review_3059580789" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3059580789" />
    <a title="Michael Gordover" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/47279941-michael-gordover"><img alt="Michael Gordover" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1443074382p2/47279941.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3059580789?book_show_action=true">Nov 23, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Michael Gordover" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Michael Gordover" href="/user/show/47279941-michael-gordover">Michael Gordover</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition 9780141921419" href="/book/show/19318079-on-painting">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3059580789" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11422741228686209482">The manuscript for all books on painting to follow<br/><br/>The compilation of thoughts on painting by a master from the 15th century. The book teaches anyone who wants to learn to paint the basics of perspective, composition, and the interplay between light and dark. Often described as the first description of perspective in art. A quick read, satisfying not only for the techniques explained but also for the historical frame of mind of the author, who often lists examples from his own time period. Fantas</span>
  <span id="freeText11422741228686209482" style="display:none">The manuscript for all books on painting to follow<br /><br />The compilation of thoughts on painting by a master from the 15th century. The book teaches anyone who wants to learn to paint the basics of perspective, composition, and the interplay between light and dark. Often described as the first description of perspective in art. A quick read, satisfying not only for the techniques explained but also for the historical frame of mind of the author, who often lists examples from his own time period. Fantastic for artists and history enthusiasts alike.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11422741228686209482" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


